The SEM image of the telson (
Fig. 20
) shows paired short plumose setae to either side of the telson nubs and associated long, erect seta dorsal to each nub. The nub magnifications show that the nubs are actually cusped and the erect setae are ringed at their tips by rows of scales. Presumably, the erect setae have a sensory function, perhaps for position within the tube and the cusped nubs may assist with gaining a purchase within the tube. Possibly the plumose setae are mechanoreceptive as well (Kauffmann 1994).
